an, 19 July 2007 \n* ''[http://www.wayanswardhani.lecture.ub.ac.id/files/2013/09/Semiotics-the-Basics.pdf  Positioning the Subject],'' ''Semiotics: The Basics'', [[Adobe Reader]] version. To reach this information (through Adobe Reader) 'Find (in this hypertext): The Positioning of the Subject'\n* ''[http://human-nature.com/reason/01/herman.pdf The Propaganda Model: A Retrospective]'', [[Edward S. Herman]], December 9, 2003\n\n[[Category:Political communication]]\n[[Category:Mass media]]\n", "name_user": "Chirag.Saluja", "label": "safe", "comment": "Minor punctuation", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Politico-media_complex"}
{"title_page": "Svinino", "text_new": "{{Infobox settlement\n|official_name          = Svinino\n|other_name             = \n|native_name            = \u0421\u0432\u0438\u043d\u0438\u043d\u043e\n|nickname               = \n|settlement_type        = Village\n|image_skyline          = \n|image_caption          = \n|pushpin_map            = Russia Vologda Oblast#Russia\n|pushpin_label_position = \n|pushpin_mapsize        =\n|pushpin_map_caption    = \n|subdivision_type       = Country\n|subdivision_name       = [[Russia]]\n|subdivision_type1      = [[List of regions of Russia|Region]] \n|subdivision_name1      = [[Vologda Oblast]]\n|subdivision_type2      = [[Counties of Russia|County]] \n|subdivision_name2      = \n|subdivision_type3      = [[Districts of Russia|District]] \n|subdivision_name3      = [[Gryazovetsky District]]\n|subdivision_type4      = [[List of municipalities of Russia|Municipality]]\n|subdivision_name4      = \n|timezone1              = \n|utc_offset1            = +3:00\n|timezone1_DST          = \n|utc_offset1_DST        = \n|postal_code_type       = \n|postal_code            = \n|elevation_m            = \n|elevation_footnotes    = \n|coordinates            = {{coord|59|03|N|40|14|E|display=inline}}<ref>[https://mapdata.ru/vologodskaya-oblast/gryazoveckiy-rayon/ \u041a\u0430\u0440\u0442\u0430 \u0413\u0440\u044f\u0437\u043e\u0432\u0435\u0446\u043a\u043e\u0433\u043e  \u0440\u0430\u0439\u043e\u043d\u0430 \u0412\u043e\u043b\u043e\u0433\u043e\u0434\u0441\u043a\u043e\u0439 \u043e\u0431\u043b\u0430\u0441\u0442\u0438]</ref>\n}}\n'''Svinino''' ({{lang-ru|\u0421\u0432\u0438\u043d\u0438\u043d\u043e}}) is a [[types of inhabited localities in Russia|rural locality]] (a [[Village#Russia|village]]) in Komyanskoye Rural Settlement, [[Gryazovetsky District]], [[Vologda Oblast]], Russia. The population was 10 as of 2002.<ref>\u0414\u0430\u043d\u043d\u044b\u0435 \u043f\u0435\u0440\u0435\u043f\u0438\u0441\u0438 2002 \u0433\u043e\u0434\u0430: \u0442\u0430\u0431\u043b\u0438\u0446\u0430 2\u0421. \u041c.: \u0424\u0435\u0434\u0435\u0440\u0430\u043b\u044c\u043d\u0430\u044f \u0441\u043b\u0443\u0436\u0431\u0430 \u0433\u043e\u0441\u0443\u0434\u0430\u0440\u0441\u0442\u0432\u0435\u043d\u043d\u043e\u0439 \u0441\u0442\u0430\u0442\u0438\u0441\u0442\u0438\u043a\u0438, 2004.</ref> \n\n== Geography ==\nThe distance to [[Gryazovets]] is 23.2&nbsp;km, to Khoroshevo is 10.7&nbsp;km.\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{Rural localities in Gryazovetsky District}}\n{{Authority control}}\n\n[[Category:Rural localities in Vologda Oblast]]\n[[Category:Rural localities in Gryazovetsky District]]\n\n\n{{VologdaOblast-geo-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox settlement\n|official_name          = Svinino\n|other_name             = \n|native_name            = \u0421\u0432\u0438\u043d\u0438\u043d\u043e\n|nickname               = \n|settlement_type        = Village\n|image_skyline          = \n|image_caption          = \n|pushpin_map            = Russia Vologda Oblast#Russia\n|pushpin_label_position = \n|pushpin_mapsize        =\n|pushpin_map_caption    = \n|subdivision_type       = Country\n|subdivision_name       = [[Russia]]\n|subdivision_type1      = [[List of regions of Russia|Region]] \n|subdivision_name1      = [[Vologda Oblast]]\n|subdivision_type2      = [[Counties of Russia|County]] \n|subdivision_name2      = \n|subdivision_type3      = [[Districts of Russia|District]] \n|subdivision_name3      = [[Gryazovetsky District]]\n|subdivision_type4      = [[List of municipalities of Russia|Municipality]]\n|subdivision_name4      = \n|timezone1              = \n|utc_offset1            = +3:00\n|timezone1_DST          = \n|utc_offset1_DST        = \n|postal_code_type       = \n|postal_code            = \n|elevation_m            = \n|elevation_footnotes    = \n|coordinates            = {{coord|59|03|N|40|14|E|display=inline}}<ref>[https://mapdata.ru/vologodskaya-oblast/gryazoveckiy-rayon/ \u041a\u0430\u0440\u0442\u0430 \u0413\u0440\u044f\u0437\u043e\u0432\u0435\u0446\u043a\u043e\u0433\u043e  \u0440\u0430\u0439\u043e\u043d\u0430 \u0412\u043e\u043b\u043e\u0433\u043e\u0434\u0441\u043a\u043e\u0439 \u043e\u0431\u043b\u0430\u0441\u0442\u0438]</ref>\n}}\n'''Svinino''' ({{lang-ru|\u0421\u0432\u0438\u043d\u0438\u043d\u043e}}) is a [[types of inhabited localities in Russia|rural locality]] (a [[Village#Russia|village]]) in Komyanskoye Rural Settlement, [[Gryazovetsky District]], [[Vologda Oblast]], Russia. The population was 10 as of 2002.<ref>\u0414\u0430\u043d\u043d\u044b\u0435 \u043f\u0435\u0440\u0435\u043f\u0438\u0441\u0438 2002 \u0433\u043e\u0434\u0430: \u0442\u0430\u0431\u043b\u0438\u0446\u0430 2\u0421. \u041c.: \u0424\u0435\u0434\u0435\u0440\u0430\u043b\u044c\u043d\u0430\u044f \u0441\u043b\u0443\u0436\u0431\u0430 \u0433\u043e\u0441\u0443\u0434\u0430\u0440\u0441\u0442\u0432\u0435\u043d\u043d\u043e\u0439 \u0441\u0442\u0430\u0442\u0438\u0441\u0442\u0438\u043a\u0438, 2004.</ref> \n\n== Geography ==\nThe distance to [[Gryazovets]] is 23.2&nbsp;km, to Khoroshevo is 10.7&nbsp;km.\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n[[Category:Rural localities in Vologda Oblast]]\n\n\n{{VologdaOblast-geo-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Wagino 20100516", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eReferences:added navigation box and category", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Svinino"}
{"title_page": "John A. Holm", "text_new": "'''John Alexander Holm''' (May 16, 1943 &ndash; December 28, 2015) was an American academic.<ref name=\"obit\" /> He was Chair of English [[Linguistics]] and History of Civilizations at the [[University of Coimbra]], [[Portugal]].<ref>[http://errol.oclc.org/laf/n82-148476.html Library of Congress Authority File ]</ref>\n\nHolm was born in [[Jackson, Michigan]] and graduated from [[Jackson High School (Michigan)|Jackson High School]] in 1961.<ref name=\"obit\" /> He received a Ph.D. in linguistics from the [[University of London]] in 1978  with his thesis \"The creole English of Nicaragua's Miskito Coast : its sociolinguistic history and a comparative study of its lexicon and syntax.\"<ref>[http://www.worldcat.org/title/creole-english-of-nicaraguas-miskito-coast-its-sociolinguistic-history-and-a-comparative-study-of-its-lexicon-and-syntax/oclc/006206227  WorldCat]</ref> He is a specialist on the history and languages of the [[Caribbean]] peoples, and the author of many books and articles  on those subjects.<ref>[http://www.worldcat.org/wcidentities/lccn-n82-148476WorldCat Authorities]</ref> He is editor with   [[Susanne Maria Michaelis]]  of the series ''Contact languages : critical concepts in language studies.'' <ref>[http://www.worldcat.org/title/contact-languages-critical-concepts-in-language-studies-vol-1/oclc/751055680&referer=brief_results Published in London & New York by Routledge, 2008-]</ref>\n\nThanks to the study of creoles, he showed that because of its importance in [[Barbados]], the white population is the starting point of most of the [[english creoles]] that are spoken by the Indian, white and black peoples in most parts of the [[Caribbean]] and [[The Carolinas|Carolina]].\n\nHe also wrote the only one dictionary of [[Bahamian English]]. He died on December 28, 2015 in Azeit\u00e3o, Portugal from prostate cancer.<ref name=\"obit\">{{cite news|last=Grimes|first=William|title=John Holm, 72, Dies; Opened Linguistics to Creole and Pidgin Tongues|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2016/01/04/us/john-holm-pioneer-in-lingustics-dies-at-72.html?rref=collection%2Fsectioncollection%2Fobituaries&action=click&contentCollection=obituaries&region=stream&module=stream_unit&version=latest&contentPlacement=5&pgtype=sectionfront|date=January 4, 2016|page=D8|access-date=April 9, 2018}}</ref>\n\n==Bibliography==\n\n{{Empty section|date=February 2013}}\n\n==Books==\n* ''Dictionary of Bahamian English,'' (with Alison Watt Shilling).   Cold Spring, N.Y.: Lexik House Publishers, 1982. {{ISBN|978-0-936368-03-0}}   <ref>[http://www.worldcat.org/title/dictionary-of-bahamian-english/oclc/008875226  WorldCat]</ref>\n* ''Central American English,'' (ed.) Heidelberg : J. Groos, 1983.\n**Review, by Steve Jones, ''Language in Society,'' Jun., 1984, vol. 13, no. 2, p.&nbsp;281\n**Review, by J. L. Dillard, '' Language'', Jun., 1985, vol. 61, no. 2, p.&nbsp;487-489\n**Review, by G. G. Gilbert, ''American Speech'' Autumn, 1985, vol. 60, no. 3, p.&nbsp;261-269\n* ''Pidgins and Creoles'' 2 vol.: v.1, \" Theory and structure\"; v.2, \"References survey\" Cambridge University Press, 1988-89  <ref>[http://www.worldcat.org/title/pidgins-and-creoles/oclc/016468410 WorldCat]</ref>\n**Review,  Morris Goodman, in ''Journal of Pidgin and Creole Language,'' vol. 7, no. 2 (1992); p.&nbsp;352-361.)\n**Review, by Salikoko S Mufwene, ''Language'', Jun., 1991, vol. 67, no. 2, p.&nbsp;380-387\n**Review by John McWhorter, ''Language in Society'', Sep., 1991, vol. 20, no. 3, p.&nbsp;477-483\n**Review, G. Sankoff, '' American Anthropologist,'' Jun., 1991, vol. 93, no. 2, p.&nbsp;511-512\n**Review, by P. Muysken, ''Journal of Linguistics,'' Sep., 1990, vol. 26, no. 2, p.&nbsp;509-512\n* ''An introduction to pidgins and creoles'' Cambridge University Press, 2000.  in 596 libraries according to  [http://www.worldcat.org/title/introduction-to-pidgin-and-creoles/oclc/056409399 WorldCat]\n**Review, by A. S. Kaye, ''Language'', Jun., 2002, vol. 78, no. 2, p.&nbsp;362-363\n* ''Languages in contact: the partial restructuring of vernaculars ''  Cambridge University Press, 2004. in 282 libraries according to  [http://www.worldcat.org/title/languages-in-contact-the-partial-restructuring-of-vernaculars/oclc/057299025 WorldCat]\n**Review by Raymond Hickey,  ''Anthropological linguistics''. 48, no. 3, (2006): 299\n**Review by Anthony P Grant,  '' Language in Society,'' Apr., 2006, vol. 35, no. 2, p.&nbsp;297-300\n**Review, by D. E. Wallcek, ''Language,'' Sep., 2006, vol. 82, no. 3, p.&nbsp;683\n*  ''Comparative Creole Syntax: Parallel Outlines of 18 Creole Grammars.'' (with  Peter L. Patrick).  [London]: Battlebridge, 2007.\n\n===Articles===\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Holm, John A.}}\n[[Category:1943 births]]\n[[Category:2015 deaths]]\n[[Category:Linguists from the United States]]\n", "text_old": "'''John Alexander Holm''' (May 16, 1943 &ndash; December 28, 2015) was an American academic.<ref name=\"obit\" /> He was Chair of English [[Linguistics]] and History of Civilizations at the [[University of Coimbra]], [[Portugal]].<ref>[http://errol.oclc.org/laf/n82-148476.html Library of Congress Authority File ]</ref>\n\nHolm was born in [[Jackson, Michigan]] and graduated from [[Jackson High School (Michigan)|Jackson High School]] in 1961.<ref name=\"obit\" /> He received a Ph.D. in linguistics from the [[University of London]] in 1978  with his thesis \"The creole English of Nicaragua's Miskito Coast : its sociolinguistic history and a comparative study of its lexicon and syntax.\"<ref>[http://www.worldcat.org/title/creole-english-of-nicaraguas-miskito-coast-its-sociolinguistic-history-and-a-comparative-study-of-its-lexicon-and-syntax/oclc/006206227  WorldCat]</ref> He is a specialist on the history and languages of the [[Caribbean]] peoples, and the author of many books and articles  on those subjects.<ref>[http://www.worldcat.org/wcidentities/lccn-n82-148476WorldCat Authorities]</ref> He is editor with   [[Susanne Maria Michaelis]]  of the series ''Contact languages : critical concepts in language studies.'' <ref>[http://www.worldcat.org/title/contact-languages-critical-concepts-in-language-studies-vol-1/oclc/751055680&referer=brief_results Published in London & New York by Routledge, 2008-]</ref>\n\nThanks to the study of creoles, he showed that because of its importance in [[Barbados]], the white population is the starting point of most of the [[english creoles]] that are spoken by the Indian, white and black peoples in most parts of the [[Caribbean]] and [[The Carolinas|Carolina]].\n\nHe also wrote the only one dictionary of [[Bahamian English]]. He died on December 28, 2015 in Azeit\u00e3o, Portugal from prostate cancer.<ref name=\"obit\">{{cite news|last=Grimes|first=William|title=John Holm, 72, Dies; Opened Linguistics to Creole and Pidgin Tongues|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2016/01/04/us/john-holm-pioneer-in-lingustics-dies-at-72.html?rref=collection%2Fsectioncollection%2Fobituaries&action=click&contentCollection=obituaries&region=stream&module=stream_unit&version=latest&contentPlacement=5&pgtype=sectionfront|date=January 4, 2016|page=D8|access-date=April 9, 2018}}</ref>\n\n==Bibliography==\n\n{{Empty section|date=February 2013}}\n\n==Books==\n* ''Dictionary of Bahamian English,'' (with Alison Watt Shilling).   Cold Spring, N.Y.: Lexik House Publishers, 1982. {{ISBN|978-0-936368-03-0}}   <ref>[http://www.worldcat.org/title/dictionary-of-bahamian-english/oclc/008875226  WorldCat]</ref>\n* ''Central American English,'' (ed.) Heidelberg : J. Groos, 1983.\n**Review, by Steve Jones, ''Language in Society,'' Jun., 1984, vol. 13, no. 2, p.&nbsp;281\n**Review, by J. L. Dillard, '' Language'', Jun., 1985, vol. 61, no. 2, p.&nbsp;487-489\n**Review, by G. G. Gilbert, ''American Speech'' Autumn, 1985, vol. 60, no. 3, p.&nbsp;261-269\n* ''Pidgins and Creoles'' 2 vol.: v.1, \" Theory and structure\"; v.2, \"References survey\" Cambridge University Press, 1988-89  <ref>[http://www.worldcat.org/title/pidgins-and-creoles/oclc/016468410 WorldCat]</ref>\n**Review,  Morris Goodman, in ''Journal of Pidgin and Creole Language,'' vol. 7, no. 2 (1992); p.&nbsp;352-361.)\n**Review, by Salikoko S Mufwene, ''Language'', Jun., 1991, vol. 67, no. 2, p.&nbsp;380-387\n**Review by John McWhorter, ''Language in Society'', Sep., 1991, vol. 20, no. 3, p.&nbsp;477-483\n**Review, G. Sankoff, '' American Anthropologist,'' Jun., 1991, vol. 93, no. 2, p.&nbsp;511-512\n**Review, by P. Muysken, ''Journal of Linguistics,'' Sep., 1990, vol. 26, no. 2, p.&nbsp;509-512\n* ''An introduction to pidgins and creoles'' Cambridge University Press, 2000.  in 596 libraries according to  [http://www.worldcat.org/title/introduction-to-pidgin-and-creoles/oclc/056409399 WorldCat]\n**Review, by A. S. Kaye, ''Language'', Jun., 2002, vol. 78, no. 2, p.&nbsp;362-363\n* ''Languages in contact: the partial restructuring of vernaculars ''  Cambridge University Press, 2004. in 282 libraries according to  [http://www.worldcat.org/title/languages-in-contact-the-partial-restructuring-of-vernaculars/oclc/057299025 WorldCat]\n**Review by Raymond Hickey,  ''Anthropological linguistics''. 48, no. 3, (2006): 299\n**Review by Anthony P Grant,  '' Language in Society,'' Apr., 2006, vol. 35, no. 2, p.&nbsp;297-300\n**Review, by D. E. Wallcek, ''Language,'' Sep., 2006, vol. 82, no. 3, p.&nbsp;683\n*  ''Comparative Creole Syntax: Parallel Outlines of 18 Creole Grammars.'' (with  Peter L. Patrick).  [London]: Battlebridge, 2007.\n\n===Articles===\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Holm, John A.}}\n[[Category:1943 births]]\n[[Category:2015 deaths]]\n[[Category:Linguists from the United States]]\n", "name_user": "Ser Amantio di Nicolao", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eReferences:add authority control", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/John_A._Holm"}
{"title_page": "Suvorovo, Gryazovetsky District, Vologda Oblast", "text_new": "{{Infobox settlement\n|official_name          = Suvorovo\n|other_name             = \n|native_name            = \u0421\u0443\u0432\u043e\u0440\u043e\u0432\u043e\n|nickname               = \n|settlement_type        = Village\n|image_skyline          = \n|image_caption          = \n|pushpin_map            = Russia Vologda Oblast#Russia\n|pushpin_label_position = \n|pushpin_mapsize        =\n|pushpin_map_caption    = \n|subdivision_type       = Country\n|subdivision_name       = [[Russia]]\n|subdivision_type1      = [[List of regions of Russia|Region]] \n|subdivision_name1      = [[Vologda Oblast]]\n|subdivision_type2      = [[Counties of Russia|County]] \n|subdivision_name2      = \n|subdivision_type3      = [[Districts of Russia|District]] \n|subdivision_name3      = [[Gryazovetsky District]]\n|subdivision_type4      = [[List of municipalities of Russia|Municipality]]\n|subdivision_name4      = \n|timezone1              = \n|utc_offset1            = +3:00\n|timezone1_DST          = \n|utc_offset1_DST        = \n|postal_code_type       = \n|postal_code            = \n|elevation_m            = \n|elevation_footnotes    = \n|coordinates            = {{coord|58|58|N|40|26|E|display=inline}}<ref>[https://mapdata.ru/vologodskaya-oblast/gryazoveckiy-rayon/ \u041a\u0430\u0440\u0442\u0430 \u0413\u0440\u044f\u0437\u043e\u0432\u0435\u0446\u043a\u043e\u0433\u043e  \u0440\u0430\u0439\u043e\u043d\u0430 \u0412\u043e\u043b\u043e\u0433\u043e\u0434\u0441\u043a\u043e\u0439 \u043e\u0431\u043b\u0430\u0441\u0442\u0438]</ref>\n}}\n'''Suvorovo''' ({{lang-ru|\u0421\u0443\u0432\u043e\u0440\u043e\u0432\u043e}}) is a [[types of inhabited localities in Russia|rural locality]] (a [[Village#Russia|village]]) in Komyanskoye Rural Settlement, [[Gryazovetsky District]], [[Vologda Oblast]], Russia. The population was 6 as of 2002.<ref>\u0414\u0430\u043d\u043d\u044b\u0435 \u043f\u0435\u0440\u0435\u043f\u0438\u0441\u0438 2002 \u0433\u043e\u0434\u0430: \u0442\u0430\u0431\u043b\u0438\u0446\u0430 2\u0421. \u041c.: \u0424\u0435\u0434\u0435\u0440\u0430\u043b\u044c\u043d\u0430\u044f \u0441\u043b\u0443\u0436\u0431\u0430 \u0433\u043e\u0441\u0443\u0434\u0430\u0440\u0441\u0442\u0432\u0435\u043d\u043d\u043e\u0439 \u0441\u0442\u0430\u0442\u0438\u0441\u0442\u0438\u043a\u0438, 2004.</ref> \n\n== Geography ==\nThe distance to [[Gryazovets]] is 33.5&nbsp;km, to Khoroshevo is 11.4&nbsp;km. Krutets is the nearest rural locality.\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{Rural localities in Gryazovetsky District}}\n{{Authority control}}\n\n[[Category:Rural localities in Vologda Oblast]]\n[[Category:Rural localities in Gryazovetsky District]]\n\n\n{{VologdaOblast-geo-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox settlement\n|official_name          = Suvorovo\n|other_name             = \n|native_name            = \u0421\u0443\u0432\u043e\u0440\u043e\u0432\u043e\n|nickname               = \n|settlement_type        = Village\n|image_skyline          = \n|image_caption          = \n|pushpin_map            = Russia Vologda Oblast#Russia\n|pushpin_label_position = \n|pushpin_mapsize        =\n|pushpin_map_caption    = \n|subdivision_type       = Country\n|subdivision_name       = [[Russia]]\n|subdivision_type1      = [[List of regions of Russia|Region]] \n|subdivision_name1      = [[Vologda Oblast]]\n|subdivision_type2      = [[Counties of Russia|County]] \n|subdivision_name2      = \n|subdivision_type3      = [[Districts of Russia|District]] \n|subdivision_name3      = [[Gryazovetsky District]]\n|subdivision_type4      = [[List of municipalities of Russia|Municipality]]\n|subdivision_name4      = \n|timezone1              = \n|utc_offset1            = +3:00\n|timezone1_DST          = \n|utc_offset1_DST        = \n|postal_code_type       = \n|postal_code            = \n|elevation_m            = \n|elevation_footnotes    = \n|coordinates            = {{coord|58|58|N|40|26|E|display=inline}}<ref>[https://mapdata.ru/vologodskaya-oblast/gryazoveckiy-rayon/ \u041a\u0430\u0440\u0442\u0430 \u0413\u0440\u044f\u0437\u043e\u0432\u0435\u0446\u043a\u043e\u0433\u043e  \u0440\u0430\u0439\u043e\u043d\u0430 \u0412\u043e\u043b\u043e\u0433\u043e\u0434\u0441\u043a\u043e\u0439 \u043e\u0431\u043b\u0430\u0441\u0442\u0438]</ref>\n}}\n'''Suvorovo''' ({{lang-ru|\u0421\u0443\u0432\u043e\u0440\u043e\u0432\u043e}}) is a [[types of inhabited localities in Russia|rural locality]] (a [[Village#Russia|village]]) in Komyanskoye Rural Settlement, [[Gryazovetsky District]], [[Vologda Oblast]], Russia. The population was 6 as of 2002.<ref>\u0414\u0430\u043d\u043d\u044b\u0435 \u043f\u0435\u0440\u0435\u043f\u0438\u0441\u0438 2002 \u0433\u043e\u0434\u0430: \u0442\u0430\u0431\u043b\u0438\u0446\u0430 2\u0421. \u041c.: \u0424\u0435\u0434\u0435\u0440\u0430\u043b\u044c\u043d\u0430\u044f \u0441\u043b\u0443\u0436\u0431\u0430 \u0433\u043e\u0441\u0443\u0434\u0430\u0440\u0441\u0442\u0432\u0435\u043d\u043d\u043e\u0439 \u0441\u0442\u0430\u0442\u0438\u0441\u0442\u0438\u043a\u0438, 2004.</ref> \n\n== Geography ==\nThe distance to [[Gryazovets]] is 33.5&nbsp;km, to Khoroshevo is 11.4&nbsp;km. Krutets is the nearest rural locality.\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n[[Category:Rural localities in Vologda Oblast]]\n\n\n{{VologdaOblast-geo-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Wagino 20100516", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eReferences:added navigation box and category", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Suvorovo,_Gryazovetsky_District,_Vologda_Oblast"}
