spils|Ventspils]]\n|match_VEN_DGD=2\u20131\n|match_VEN_GUL=1\u20131\n|match_VEN_JEL=0\u20130\n|match_VEN_FCJ=2\u20130\n|match_VEN_JVV=4\u20131\n|match_VEN_LIE=1\u20132\n|match_VEN_RFS=4\u20130\n|match_VEN_SKO=0\u20130\n\n|match_DGD_GUL_note=Match took place in [[Gulbene]]. Placed as a Daugava home match for organizational purposes. \n\n|match_JVV_DGD_note=This match was cancelled and awarded to Daugava 0-3 due to Jurmala-VV being unable to field a team for the match.<ref>{{cite web|title=Virsl\u012bga 2011: FK J\u016brmala V.V. - FC Daugava (sp\u0113le atcelta)|url=http://www.lff.lv/lv/virsliga/fixtures/2011/lap3/match96/|publisher=LFF|accessdate=28 August 2011}}</ref>\n\n|update=complete\n|source=[http://www.lff.lv/lv/virsliga/fixtures/2011/ Latvian Football Federation] {{in lang|lv}}\n}}\n\n===Relegation play-offs===\nAt the season's end, the 9th place club in the Latvian Higher League will face the runners-up of the Latvian First League in a two-legged playoff, with the winner being awarded a spot in the 2012 Higher League competition.\n\n{{football box\n|date= 10 November 2011\n|time= 16:00\n|team1= [[Olimps/RFS]]\n|score  =1\u20132\n|report=\n|team2= [[FK Spartaks J\u016brmala|Spartaks]]\n|goals1=Bl\u016bms {{goal|72}}\n|goals2={{goal|14}} Rua<br/>{{goal|21}} Panasjuks\n|stadium=\n|attendance=\n|referee=\n}}\n----\n{{football box\n|date= 13 November 2011\n|time= 14:00\n|team1= [[FK Spartaks J\u016brmala|Spartaks]]\n|score= 2\u20130\n|report=\n|team2= [[Olimps/RFS]]\n|goals1=Budilovs {{goal|32}}<br>Skalenko {{goal|49|pen.}}\n|goals2=\n|stadium=\n|attendance=\n|referee=\n}}\n\n==Top goalscorers==\n''Source: [http://www.lff.lv/lv/virsliga/tabula2011/ LMT Virsl\u012bga 2011] {{in lang|lv}}''\n{|class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n!Rank\n!Player\n!Club\n!Goals\n|-\n|align=\"center\" |1\n| {{flagicon|Brazil}} [[Nathan J\u00fanior Soares de Carvalho|Nathan J\u00fanior]]\n| [[Skonto FC|Skonto Riga]]\n|align=\"center\"|22\n|-\n|align=\"center\" |2\n| {{flagicon|Georgia}} Mamuka Gh